slots.name: equilibrium
slots.description: A system is in equilibrium if no changes occur if it is isolated from  its surroundings

slots.name: closed
slots.description: A closed thermodynamic system contains a macrocopic amount of matter.  There is no mass flow across its boundary, the mass of the system is constant.  Work and heat can be transferred across the system's boundary. The boundary  can be a real object (e.g. walls) or we can just imagine it. The system can  move freely in space. Everything outside the system is called "surroundings".

slots.name: homogeneous
slots.description: A system is homogenous if at all locations inside the system all intesive  state variables have the same value.

slots.name: TechnicalWorkEquation_as_text
slots.ifabsent: string(w_t_{change_of_state#transition} = w_i_{change_of_state#transition} + w_a_{change_of_state#transition} + p_{change_of_state#final_state} * v_{change_of_state#final_state} - p_{change_of_state#initial_state} * v_{change_of_state#initial_state})

slots.name: DelSPerfectGasVolumeEquation_as_text
slots.ifabsent: string(del_s_{change_of_state#transition} = c_v_{system#material} * ln(T_{change_of_state#final_state} / T_{change_of_state#initial_state}) + R_{system#material} * ln(v_{change_of_state#final_state} / v_{change_of_state#initial_state}))

slots.name: DelSPerfectGasVolumeEquationII_as_text
slots.ifabsent: string(del_s_{change_of_state#transition} = c_vm_{system#material} * ln(T_{change_of_state#final_state} / T_{change_of_state#initial_state}) + Rbar_{system#material} * ln(v_{change_of_state#final_state} / v_{change_of_state#initial_state}))

classes.name: System
classes.description: Is the part of the universe, we are studying.

classes.name: ClosedSystem
classes.description: A closed thermodynamic system contains a macrocopic amount of matter.  There is no mass flow across its boundary, the mass of the system is constant.  Work and heat can be transferred across the system's boundary. The boundary  can be a real object (e.g. walls) or we can just imagine it. The system can  move freely in space. Everything outside the system is called "surroundings".

classes.name: OpenSystem
classes.description: An open system is a fixed part of the space that we are interested in.  Work and heat as well as matter can be transferred across its boundary.

classes.name: PureMaterial
classes.description: A pure material consists of one homogeneous substance with certain material behaviour properties.

classes.name: Mixture
classes.description: A mixture consist of multiple (pure) substances.

classes.name: EquationOfState
classes.description: An EoS is the relation between functions of state, such as temperature (T), pressure (P), volume (V), internal energy or specific heat.  It characterizes the state of matter of a material under a given set of physical conditions.  (https://serc.carleton.edu/NAGTWorkshops/mineralogy/mineral_physics/eos.html)

classes.name: State
classes.description: The thermodynamic state of a system is characterized by macroscopic,  measurable properties sufficient to determine all other  macroscopic properties.

classes.name: Transition
classes.description: We define transition as the change of one equilibrium state to another.  The transistion may or may not be reversible.

classes.name: ChangeOfState
classes.description: In a "change of state" a system undergoes a change from one equilibirum state  (initial state) to another (final state). The transistion between these states  may or may not be reversible.

classes.name: DerivedVariable
classes.description: A variable which can be mathematically derived.

classes.name: StateVariable
classes.description: Measurable variables that characterize the state of a system.

classes.name: ChangeOfStateVariable
classes.description: Measurable variables that characterize the change of state of a system.

classes.name: MaterialProperty
classes.description: Properties that describe a material.

classes.name: UniversalQuantity
classes.description: Variable that always has the same value.

classes.name: SpecificProperty
classes.description: Specific properties are extensive properties per unit mass.  We denote them by lower case letters.

classes.name: ExtensiveStateVariable
classes.description: The value of an extensive property of a homogenous system is  proportional to the mass of the system.  We denote them by upper case letters.

classes.name: IntensiveStateVariable
classes.description: The value of an intensive property of a homogenous system does  not vary with the mass of the system.

classes.name: InternalStateVariable
classes.description: Describes the state of a system that does not move.

classes.name: ExternalStateVariable
classes.description: External state variables are state variables that depend on the internal state variables of the systems  and its interactions with the surroundings.

classes.name: Heat
classes.description: Heat is energy transferred due to temperature differences only.
